<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-04-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-04-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 LO/4–750: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d445fn1">Repeated Paris 1533, <gloss target="#t_HICOG1">HICOG</gloss> 2385.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-04-07T19:00:00-05:00">April
                                        7, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1573. Fol agreement with Fr and Brit Embs schedule May mtg: Secy
                                arrive Paris May 7 for discussions May 8 Schuman; proceeding London
                                for discussions May 9–10 Bevin; with Bevin and Schuman May 11, 12,
                                13; <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> Council mtg May 15, 16 and
                                17. (<gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> govts have been asked to
                                confirm.) Advance party probably commencing preparatory talks Apr 24
                                Lond. As Fr have agreed sending Advanced group Lond all preparatory
                                talks will probably be held there. You will be informed soonest
                                composition groups.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>